LUMUS

Feb 10

Tab & URL Behavior 

General concept

The calculator selector (Enskildfirma / Anställning / Kryptoskatt) must be implemented as a tab interface, not as buttons.
	•	Tabs represent different modes of the same calculator
	•	There is one shared page layout
	•	Only the active tab state, form fields, calculation logic, and “Så räknar vi” content change

The attached images show the visual reference for the tab states.

⸻

URL ↔ Tab Mapping

Each tab must be directly connected to a URL.

URL rules
	•	/enskildfirma → Enskildfirma tab is active
	•	/anstallning → Anställning tab is active
	•	/kryptoskatt → Kryptoskatt tab is active
	•	/ (root) → defaults to Enskildfirma

Behavior
	•	Visiting a URL must automatically activate the corresponding tab
	•	Switching tabs must update the URL without a full page reload
	•	The page layout must remain identical across all URLs

⸻

Tab Switching Logic

When a tab is selected (by click or by URL):
	1.	Activate the corresponding tab visually
	2.	Show the correct form fields for that calculator
	3.	Use the correct calculation logic
	4.	Render the matching “Så räknar vi” explanation below
	5.	Keep header, calculator card container, and footer unchanged

This is one component with multiple states, not separate pages.

⸻

Visual Rules for Tabs 

Active tab (selected state)

As shown in the images Tab example URL Enskildfirma.png and Tab example URL krypto.png:
	•	Background color = same gradient/background as the calculator card
	•	Tab visually merges into the top edge of the card
	•	No bottom border (the card continues from the tab)
	•	Text and icon are white
	•	Active tab appears visually “attached” to the card

Inactive tabs

As shown in the images:
	•	Background = page background (off-white)
	•	Thin outline/border in brand color
	•	Text and icon in brand color
	•	Inactive tabs sit slightly above the card
	•	They do not visually connect to the card

Important
	•	Tabs must not look like primary action buttons
	•	No hover animations that suggest a CTA
	•	The visual difference between active and inactive tabs must be clear at a glance

⸻

Layout Rules
	•	Tabs are positioned directly above the calculator card
	•	Tabs are horizontally aligned
	•	Only one tab can be active at a time
	•	The calculator card always stays in the same position

⸻

Calculator Card Background — Color & Gradient Rules

Background color of the calculator card

The calculator card uses a horizontal linear gradient.

Gradient values (left → right):
	•	Start color: #7E8EC6
	•	End color: #6389C6

Usage rules
	•	This gradient is used for:
	•	the full calculator card background
	•	the active tab background (must visually merge with the card)
	•	The gradient direction must be consistent across:
	•	all calculator modes
	•	all URLs
	•	all screen sizes

Contrast rules
	•	All text and form fields inside the gradient card use:
	•	white (#FFFFFF) for text
	•	white backgrounds for inputs
	•	Icons inside the active tab are white
	•	Inactive tabs do not use the gradient

Important consistency rule

The gradient is part of the core visual identity and must never:
	•	change between tabs
	•	change between URLs
	•	be replaced with a flat color

⸻

Summary (single sentence)

This interface is one calculator with three tab-based modes, where each mode is addressable via its own URL and visually indicated by a tab that merges into the calculator card when active.  
Så räknar vi part

Implement the “Så räknar vi” breakdown according to the visual guideline.

Reference image (visual guide):
https://github.com/Lillyriemer/skatto/blob/main/Sa%20raknar%20vi%20visual%20guideline.png?raw=true

General rule:
“Så räknar vi” is a user-facing explanation layer that appears below the calculator results. It should be readable, sectional, calm, editorial, and not look like a debug dump or raw data list.

Structural requirements:
	1.	Show an initial summary paragraph that reads like a calm explanation, not a list. Example structure:
	•	Lägg undan totalt: X kr
	•	Skatt/avgifter: Y kr
	•	Momsnetto: Z kr
	•	Redan betald preliminärskatt: -W kr
	2.	Provide a toggle link labeled “Visa hela beräkningen” that expands a more detailed breakdown when clicked.
	3.	The expanded breakdown must be structured into three clear sections with headings (as shown in the visual guideline):
	•	ÖVERSKOTT
• Vinst
• Schablonavdrag
→ Överskott (bold)
	•	BESKATTNINGSBAR INKOMST
• Överskott
• Grundavdrag
→ Beskattningsbar inkomst (bold)
	•	SLUTLIG SKATT
• Egenavgifter
• Nedsättning av egenavgifter
• Kommunalskatt
• Betald preliminärskatt
• Moms
→ Total skattefordran / kvarskatt (bold)
	4.	At the bottom of the detailed breakdown, include reference text listing the data sources (plain text, not values):
	•	Egenavgifter
	•	Grundavdrag
	•	Schablonavdrag
	•	Kommunalskatt (SCB)
	•	Statlig inkomstskatt
	•	Jobbskatteavdrag
	•	Skattereduktion förvärvsinkomst
	•	Nedsättning av egenavgifter

Visual rules (exactly as in the guideline):
• Section headings use uppercase letter style, spacing, and font weight consistent with the guideline.
• Values are aligned to the right.
• Only final totals (section subtotals) should be bold.
• Use spacing between items and sections to create room and clarity — do not cram items together.
• No border boxes, no horizontal rules except subtle separators between major sections.

Behavior:
	•	The detailed breakdown is hidden initially.
	•	Clicking “Visa hela beräkningen” expands the breakdown inline.
	•	This section is purely informational and does not trigger recalculation.
	•	If values are zero or empty, still show sections according to the structure with zeros, not removed items.

Purpose reminder:
“Så räknar vi” is an explanation for the user, not a raw data log. It must feel calm, clear, and trustworthy.

  Footer — Global Component Instructions for Lumus

Current issue

The footer is currently rendered as a simple text block (see first reference image).
This is not correct and does not match the Skatto visual identity.

The footer must be replaced by a designed, branded footer section as shown in the second reference image.

⸻

Footer Concept (Important)

The footer is a visual closing section, not just navigation.

It represents:
	•	“krångel” (complexity)
	•	turning into clarity
	•	calm ending of the page

The footer must feel intentional, graphic, and consistent across all pages.

⸻

Footer Structure (Top → Bottom)

1. Graphic section (background / top part)

At the top of the footer, render a static graphic image provided by design.

This image will include:
	•	the krångel illustration
	•	the Skatto logo
	•	the slogan “SKATT, UTAN KRÅNGEL.”

The graphic is provided here skatto_footer image.png and must be rendered as-is.

Rules:
	•	No text is recreated manually inside this graphic
	•	No overlays, no additional elements
	•	The graphic spans the full width of the content area
	•	Background color matches the page background (#F8F9FD)

⸻

2. Footer content below the graphic

Directly below the graphic, render the footer content in plain HTML.

Footer menu
Show a simple horizontal text menu with the following links:
	•	Om Skatto
	•	Kontakt
	•	Integritetspolicy
	•	Villkor
	•	Cookies

Rules:
	•	Text-only links (no buttons)
	•	Brand color text (#6389C6)
	•	Calm, low visual weight
	•	Same menu appears on all pages

⸻

3. Disclaimer text

Below the menu, render the disclaimer text:

Skatto är ett beräkningsverktyg som ger uppskattningar baserat på gällande schabloner.
Resultaten ersätter inte rådgivning från Skatteverket eller redovisningskonsult.

Rules:
	•	Smaller font size than menu
	•	Neutral text color
	•	Clearly readable but visually secondary
	•	No background box

⸻

4. Footer scope & reuse
	•	This footer component appears on all pages
	•	The footer is identical across:
	•	/
	•	/enskildfirma
	•	/anstallning
	•	/kryptoskatt
	•	No variation per calculator

⸻

Visual Consistency Rules
	•	Footer background blends into the page background
	•	No hard separators or boxed containers
	•	The footer should feel like a soft landing, not a hard stop

⸻

Summary (important)

The footer is a designed closing section with:
	1.	One static graphic (krångel + logo + slogan)
	2.	A simple text menu
	3.	A legal disclaimer

It must not look like default site chrome or autogenerated layout.
 
